{
  "updated_summary": "Under a stormy sky, the Blue Cat, with the New Mouse Character clinging to his back, swings a rope toward a dark cloud, causing it to rain water into a wooden bucket on a stone parapet. Meanwhile, in a dimly lit stone corridor, the Wicked Witch of the West, cackling menacingly, taunts Dorothy, the Scarecrow, the Tin Man, and the Cowardly Lion before conjuring a fiery spell that engulfs them. As the Scarecrow screams, "I'm burning!", the Blue Cat, now drenched and struggling with an electrified rope, is yanked violently toward the parapet's edge, the New Mouse Character desperately clinging to him."
}
